<h1>1 Art of bhilala community</h1>
    <p>
        The Bhilala community is known for its rich traditional art and culture.
        One of the most famous art forms is Pithora painting, which is made on walls
        using bright natural colors. These paintings show animals, festivals, gods,
        and daily village life. Bhilala art also includes folk music, dance, and
        handmade decorative crafts that reflect their cultural heritage and traditions.
    </p>
    <h1>2 Location of Bhilala Community</h1>
    <p>
        The Bhilala community is mainly found in Madhya Pradesh, especially in
        districts like Jhabua, Alirajpur, Dhar, Barwani, and Khargone. They are
        also present in parts of Gujarat, Rajasthan, and Maharashtra. Most Bhilala
        people live in rural and tribal areas where agriculture is the main occupation.
    </p>
