<h1>4 Language of Bhilala Community</h1>
    <p>
        The Bhilala community mainly speaks Bhilali or Bhilala dialects, which are
        related to the Bhili language group. Many Bhilala people also speak Hindi
        and regional languages such as Marathi or Gujarati, depending on the state
        where they live. Their language is an important part of their cultural identity
        and helps preserve their traditions.
    </p>
